449  }

497 /// copy constructor implementation
498 Integer::Integer(const Integer &obj) {
499  /// object member can be just copied by value
500  this->value = obj.value;
501  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
502  if (obj.macro) {
503  this->macro.reset(obj.macro->clone());
504  }
505 
506  /// if there is a token, make copy
507  if (obj.token) {
508  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
509  }
510 
511  /// set parents
512  set_parent_in_children();
513 }

2362 /**
2363  * \brief Erase member to definitions
2364  */
2365 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator
2366 AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(
2367  AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator first) {
2368  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, first);
2369  return definitions.erase(first_it);
2370 }
2371 /**
2372  * \brief Erase members to definitions
2373  */
2374 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator
2375 AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(
2376  AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator first,
2377  AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator last) {
2378  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, first);
2379  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, last);
2380  return definitions.erase(first_it, last_it);
2381 }
2382 /**
2383  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to definitions
2384  *
2385  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
2386  */
2387 size_t AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(
2388  std::unordered_set<AssignedDefinition *> &to_be_erased) {
2389  auto first = definitions.begin();
2390  auto last = definitions.end();
2391  auto result = first;
2392 
2393  while (first != last) {
2394  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
2395  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
2396  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
2397  reset_assigned_definition(result, *first);
2398  ++result;
2399  }
2400  ++first;
2401  }
2402 
2403  size_t out = last - result;
2404  erase_assigned_definition(result, last);
2405 
2406  return out;
2407 }
2408 
2409 /**
2410  * \brief Insert member to definitions
2411  */
2412 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator
2413 AssignedBlock::insert_assigned_definition(
2414  AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator position,
2415  const std::shared_ptr<AssignedDefinition> &n) {
2416  n->set_parent(this);
2417  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, position);
2418  return definitions.insert(pos_it, n);
2419 }

2426  // set parents
2427  n->set_parent(this);
2428 
2429  definitions[position - definitions.begin()].reset(n);
2430 }

2922 /**
2923  * \brief Erase members to statements
2924  */
2925 StatementVector::const_iterator
2926 StatementBlock::erase_statement(StatementVector::const_iterator first,
2927  StatementVector::const_iterator last) {
2928  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(statements, first);
2929  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(statements, last);
2930  return statements.erase(first_it, last_it);
2931 }
2932 /**
2933  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to statements
2934  *
2935  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
2936  */
2937 size_t
2938 StatementBlock::erase_statement(std::unordered_set<Statement *> &to_be_erased) {
2939  auto first = statements.begin();
2940  auto last = statements.end();
2941  auto result = first;
2942 
2943  while (first != last) {
2944  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
2945  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
2946  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
2947  reset_statement(result, *first);
2948  ++result;
2949  }
2950  ++first;
2951  }
2952 
2953  size_t out = last - result;
2954  erase_statement(result, last);
2955 
2956  return out;
2957 }

3022 StatementBlock::StatementBlock(const StatementBlock &obj) {
3023  /// copy each element of vector
3024  for (auto &item : obj.statements) {
3025  this->statements.emplace_back(item->clone());
3026  }
3027 
3028  /// if there is a token, make copy
3029  if (obj.token) {
3030  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
3031  }
3032 
3033  /// set parents
3034  set_parent_in_children();
3035 }

6420  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
6421  if (obj.rhs) {
6422  this->rhs.reset(obj.rhs->clone());
6423  }
6424 
6425  /// if there is a token, make copy

6702  this->rhs.reset(obj.rhs->clone());
6703  }

6706  if (obj.token) {
6707  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
6708  }
6709 
6710  /// set parents
6711  set_parent_in_children();
6712 }

6723  rhs->set_parent(this);

6914 /// copy constructor implementation
6915 FunctionCall::FunctionCall(const FunctionCall &obj) {
6916  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
6917  if (obj.name) {
6918  this->name.reset(obj.name->clone());
6919  }
6920  /// copy each element of vector
6921  for (auto &item : obj.arguments) {
6922  this->arguments.emplace_back(item->clone());
6923  }
6924 
6925  /// if there is a token, make copy
6926  if (obj.token) {
6927  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
6928  }
6929 
6930  /// set parents
6931  set_parent_in_children();
6932 }

6937  /// optional member could be nullptr
6938  if (name) {
6939  name->set_parent(this);
6940  }
6941  /// set parent for each element of the vector
6942  for (auto &item : arguments) {
6943  item->set_parent(this);
6944  }
6945 }

7436  (void)v;
7437  /// optional member could be nullptr
7438  if (this->gt) {
7439  this->gt->accept(v);
7440  }
7441  (void)v;
7442  /// optional member could be nullptr
7443  if (this->unit2) {
7444  this->unit2->accept(v);
7445  }
7446  (void)v;
7447 }

7796 /**
7797  * \brief Erase member to variables
7798  */
7799 LocalVarVector::const_iterator
7800 LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
7801  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
7802  return variables.erase(first_it);
7803 }
7804 /**
7805  * \brief Erase members to variables
7806  */
7807 LocalVarVector::const_iterator
7808 LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first,
7809  LocalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
7810  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
7811  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(variables, last);
7812  return variables.erase(first_it, last_it);
7813 }
7814 /**
7815  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
7816  *
7817  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
7818  */
7819 size_t LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(
7820  std::unordered_set<LocalVar *> &to_be_erased) {
7821  auto first = variables.begin();
7822  auto last = variables.end();
7823  auto result = first;
7824 
7825  while (first != last) {
7826  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
7827  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
7828  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
7829  reset_local_var(result, *first);
7830  ++result;
7831  }
7832  ++first;
7833  }
7834 
7835  size_t out = last - result;
7836  erase_local_var(result, last);
7837 
7838  return out;
7839 }
7840 
7841 /**
7842  * \brief Insert member to variables
7843  */
7844 LocalVarVector::const_iterator
7845 LocalListStatement::insert_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position,
7846  const std::shared_ptr<LocalVar> &n) {
7847  n->set_parent(this);
7848  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(variables, position);
7849  return variables.insert(pos_it, n);
7850 }
7851 
7852 /**
7853  * \brief Reset member to variables
7854  */
7855 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(
7856  LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, LocalVar *n) {
7857  // set parents
7858  n->set_parent(this);
7859 
7860  variables[position - variables.begin()].reset(n);
7861 }
7862 
7863 /**
7864  * \brief Reset member to variables
7865  */
7866 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(
7867  LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<LocalVar> n) {
7868  // set parents
7869  n->set_parent(this);
7870 
7871  variables[position - variables.begin()] = n;
7872 }

8460  this->values.emplace_back(item->clone());

9925 void IfStatement::visit_children(visitor::Visitor &v) {
9926  /// use -> for pointer member
9927  condition->accept(v);
9928  (void)v;
9929  /// use -> for pointer member
9930  statement_block->accept(v);
9931  (void)v;
9932  /// visit each element of vector
9933  for (auto &item : this->elseifs) {
9934  item->accept(v);
9935  }
9936  (void)v;
9937  /// optional member could be nullptr
9938  if (this->elses) {
9939  this->elses->accept(v);
9940  }
9941  (void)v;
9942 }

9951  /// visit each element of vector

9985 /// copy constructor implementation
9986 IfStatement::IfStatement(const IfStatement &obj) {
9987  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
9988  if (obj.condition) {
9989  this->condition.reset(obj.condition->clone());
9990  }
9991  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
9992  if (obj.statement_block) {
9993  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());
9994  }
9995  /// copy each element of vector
9996  for (auto &item : obj.elseifs) {
9997  this->elseifs.emplace_back(item->clone());
9998  }
9999  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
10000  if (obj.elses) {
10001  this->elses.reset(obj.elses->clone());
10002  }
10003 
10004  /// if there is a token, make copy
10005  if (obj.token) {
10006  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
10007  }
10008 
10009  /// set parents
10010  set_parent_in_children();
10011 }
10012 
10013 /// set this parent in the children
10014 void IfStatement::set_parent_in_children() {
10015 
10016  /// optional member could be nullptr
10017  if (condition) {
10018  condition->set_parent(this);
10019  }
10020  /// optional member could be nullptr
10021  if (statement_block) {
10022  statement_block->set_parent(this);
10023  }
10024  /// set parent for each element of the vector
10025  for (auto &item : elseifs) {
10026  item->set_parent(this);
10027  }
10028  /// optional member could be nullptr
10029  if (elses) {
10030  elses->set_parent(this);
10031  }
10032 }

10806 /**
10807  * \brief Erase member to statements
10808  */
10809 WatchVector::const_iterator
10810 WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first) {
10811  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(statements, first);
10812  return statements.erase(first_it);
10813 }
10814 /**
10815  * \brief Erase members to statements
10816  */
10817 WatchVector::const_iterator
10818 WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first,
10819  WatchVector::const_iterator last) {
10820  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(statements, first);
10821  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(statements, last);
10822  return statements.erase(first_it, last_it);
10823 }
10824 /**
10825  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to statements
10826  *
10827  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
10828  */
10829 size_t WatchStatement::erase_watch(std::unordered_set<Watch *> &to_be_erased) {
10830  auto first = statements.begin();
10831  auto last = statements.end();
10832  auto result = first;
10833 
10834  while (first != last) {
10835  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
10836  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
10837  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
10838  reset_watch(result, *first);
10839  ++result;
10840  }
10841  ++first;
10842  }
10843 
10844  size_t out = last - result;
10845  erase_watch(result, last);
10846 
10847  return out;
10848 }
10849

10851  * \brief Insert member to statements
10852  */
10853 WatchVector::const_iterator
10854 WatchStatement::insert_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator position,
10855  const std::shared_ptr<Watch> &n) {
10856  n->set_parent(this);
10857  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(statements, position);
10858  return statements.insert(pos_it, n);
10859 }

10869  statements[position - statements.begin()].reset(n);
10870 }

11220 /// copy constructor implementation
11221 Compartment::Compartment(const Compartment &obj) {
11222  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11223  if (obj.name) {
11224  this->name.reset(obj.name->clone());
11225  }
11226  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11227  if (obj.expression) {
11228  this->expression.reset(obj.expression->clone());
11229  }
11230  /// copy each element of vector
11231  for (auto &item : obj.names) {
11232  this->names.emplace_back(item->clone());
11233  }
11234 
11235  /// if there is a token, make copy
11236  if (obj.token) {
11237  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
11238  }
11239 
11240  /// set parents
11241  set_parent_in_children();
11242 }

11251  /// optional member could be nullptr
11252  if (expression) {
11253  expression->set_parent(this);
11254  }
11255  /// set parent for each element of the vector
11256  for (auto &item : names) {
11257  item->set_parent(this);
11258  }
11259 }

11466  this->reaction2->accept(v);
11467  }
11468  (void)v;

11470  expression1->accept(v);
11471  (void)v;

11474  this->expression2->accept(v);
11475  }
11476  (void)v;
11477 }

11530 ReactionStatement::ReactionStatement(const ReactionStatement &obj) {
11531  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11532  if (obj.reaction1) {
11533  this->reaction1.reset(obj.reaction1->clone());
11534  }
11535  /// object member can be just copied by value
11536  this->op = obj.op;
11537  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11538  if (obj.reaction2) {
11539  this->reaction2.reset(obj.reaction2->clone());
11540  }
11541  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11542  if (obj.expression1) {
11543  this->expression1.reset(obj.expression1->clone());
11544  }
11545  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11546  if (obj.expression2) {
11547  this->expression2.reset(obj.expression2->clone());
11548  }
11549 
11550  /// if there is a token, make copy
11551  if (obj.token) {
11552  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
11553  }
11554 
11555  /// set parents
11556  set_parent_in_children();
11557 }

12022  }
12023  /// copy each element of vector
12024  for (auto &item : obj.depend_vars) {
12025  this->depend_vars.emplace_back(item->clone());
12026  }

12029  this->from.reset(obj.from->clone());
12030  }

12033  this->to.reset(obj.to->clone());
12034  }

12037  this->with.reset(obj.with->clone());
12038  }
12039 
12040  /// if there is a token, make copy
12041  if (obj.token) {
12042  this->token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
12043  }
12044 
12045  /// set parents
12046  set_parent_in_children();
12047 }

12781 /**
12782  * \brief Erase member to variables
12783  */
12784 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator
12785 Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
12786  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
12787  return variables.erase(first_it);
12788 }
12789 /**
12790  * \brief Erase members to variables
12791  */
12792 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator
12793 Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first,
12794  GlobalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
12795  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
12796  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(variables, last);
12797  return variables.erase(first_it, last_it);
12798 }
12799 /**
12800  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
12801  *
12802  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
12803  */
12804 size_t Global::erase_global_var(std::unordered_set<GlobalVar *> &to_be_erased) {
12805  auto first = variables.begin();
12806  auto last = variables.end();
12807  auto result = first;
12808 
12809  while (first != last) {
12810  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
12811  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
12812  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
12813  reset_global_var(result, *first);
12814  ++result;
12815  }
12816  ++first;
12817  }
12818 
12819  size_t out = last - result;
12820  erase_global_var(result, last);
12821 
12822  return out;
12823 }
12824 
12825 /**
12826  * \brief Insert member to variables
12827  */
12828 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator
12829 Global::insert_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator position,
12830  const std::shared_ptr<GlobalVar> &n) {
12831  n->set_parent(this);
12832  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(variables, position);
12833  return variables.insert(pos_it, n);
12834 }
12835 
12836 /**
12837  * \brief Reset member to variables
12838  */
12839 void Global::reset_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator position,
12840  GlobalVar *n) {
12841  // set parents
12842  n->set_parent(this);
12843 
12844  variables[position - variables.begin()].reset(n);
12845 }
12846 
12847 /**
12848  * \brief Reset member to variables
12849  */
12850 void Global::reset_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator position,
12851  std::shared_ptr<GlobalVar> n) {
12852  // set parents
12853  n->set_parent(this);
12854 
12855  variables[position - variables.begin()] = n;
12856 }

13516  */
13517 void Program::emplace_back_node(std::shared_ptr<Node> n) {

13519  // set parents
13520  n->set_parent(this);

13522 
13523 /**
13524  * \brief Erase member to blocks
13525  */
13526 NodeVector::const_iterator
13527 Program::erase_node(NodeVector::const_iterator first) {
13528  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(blocks, first);
13529  return blocks.erase(first_it);
13530 }
13531 /**
13532  * \brief Erase members to blocks
13533  */
13534 NodeVector::const_iterator
13535 Program::erase_node(NodeVector::const_iterator first,
13536  NodeVector::const_iterator last) {
13537  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(blocks, first);
13538  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(blocks, last);
13539  return blocks.erase(first_it, last_it);
13540 }
13541 /**
13542  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to blocks
13543  *
13544  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
13545  */
13546 size_t Program::erase_node(std::unordered_set<Node *> &to_be_erased) {
13547  auto first = blocks.begin();
13548  auto last = blocks.end();
13549  auto result = first;
13550 
13551  while (first != last) {
13552  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
13553  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
13554  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
13555  reset_node(result, *first);
13556  ++result;
13557  }
13558  ++first;
13559  }
13560 
13561  size_t out = last - result;
13562  erase_node(result, last);
13563 
13564  return out;
13565 }
13566 
13567 /**
13568  * \brief Insert member to blocks
13569  */
13570 NodeVector::const_iterator
13571 Program::insert_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position,
13572  const std::shared_ptr<Node> &n) {
13573  n->set_parent(this);
13574  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(blocks, position);
13575  return blocks.insert(pos_it, n);
13576 }
13577 
13578 /**
13579  * \brief Reset member to blocks
13580  */
13581 void Program::reset_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position, Node *n) {
13582  // set parents
13583  n->set_parent(this);
13584 
13585  blocks[position - blocks.begin()].reset(n);
13586 }
13587 
13588 /**
13589  * \brief Reset member to blocks
13590  */
13591 void Program::reset_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position,
13592  std::shared_ptr<Node> n) {
13593  // set parents
13594  n->set_parent(this);
13595 
13596  blocks[position - blocks.begin()] = n;
13597 }

13637 }
